  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Patients with stage-I multiple myeloma are treated with a vaccine made from their own immune
      cells (dendritic cells) and their own myeloma protein. Vaccinations are given on 5 occasions
      every 4 weeks. The aim is to induce an immune reaction against the malignant myeloma cells in
      order to slow down or cure the disease.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
